    <item>
      <title>美国房地产危机消退，信贷损失下降，加拿大帝国商业银行表现优异</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-12-05/cibc-beats-as-credit-losses-decline-despite-economic-concerns</link>
      <description><![CDATA[加拿大帝国商业银行 (Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce) 的信用质量又一个季度好于预期，其美国业务显示出克服商业房地产问题迹象，其业绩超出预期。股价上涨。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-12-05/cibc-beats-as-credit-losses-decline-despite-economic-concerns</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 05 Dec 2024 10:42:58 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>对冲基金让 MicroStrategy 成为华尔街最热门的交易</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-12-05/convertible-bond-arbs-are-making-microstrategy-wall-street-s-hottest-trade</link>
      <description><![CDATA[为了满足自己对比特币数十亿美元的狂热需求，迈克尔·塞勒 (Michael Saylor) 已经利用了散户投资者的需求，这些投资者对 MicroStrategy Inc. 今年超过 500% 的涨幅十分着迷。他还从对冲基金那里获益，这些对冲基金对比特币的交易地点并不那么在意。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-12-05/convertible-bond-arbs-are-making-microstrategy-wall-street-s-hottest-trade</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 05 Dec 2024 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>OPEC+ 计划推迟且放缓产量恢复速度，油价小幅上涨</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-12-04/latest-oil-market-news-and-analysis-for-dec-5</link>
      <description><![CDATA[油价经历了波动，在 OPEC+ 宣布计划推迟三个月增加供应后，油价小幅走高，但仍将从 4 月份开始向预计供应过剩的市场增加石油供应。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-12-04/latest-oil-market-news-and-analysis-for-dec-5</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 04 Dec 2024 23:34:00 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>前贸易主管称特朗普喜欢关税，但加拿大可以对石油进行反击</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-12-04/trump-loves-tariffs-but-canada-can-strike-back-on-oil-ex-trade-chief-says</link>
      <description><![CDATA[曾在唐纳德·特朗普第一任期内领导加拿大贸易谈判团队的人士表示，美国当选总统“现在更喜欢关税”，而且在他的第二任期内，使用关税将不会受到太多限制。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-12-04/trump-loves-tariffs-but-canada-can-strike-back-on-oil-ex-trade-chief-says</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 04 Dec 2024 22:47:56 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
